title: Search for local land charges on land and property

heading_context: Search for local land charges on land and property
chunks.html_content:
Local land charges can restrict the way you use land and property. Examples include:

  • planning conditions
  • highways agreements
  • tree preservation orders
  • conservation areas
  • listed buildings
  • environmental health notices

Use this service to check for local land charges in England and Wales.

This service is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).

chunks.html_content:
You’ll need to create an account to use this service.

It’s free to do a search but you can pay £15 for an official search certificate.

You can contact HM Land Registry with any queries about using this service.
